Two children died after they were burnt in their house in Usoga village, Bondo sub-county.  The two, Roseline Adhiambo and Maryanne Akoth, were sleeping in their house when the incident happened.  According to the West Yimbo chief Paul Olang' said the children's mother Nancy Awuor was not at home during the incident.  Bondo sub-county police boss Roseline Chebosho told The Standard that the fire started and spread fast to the mattress where the children were sleeping.  Race for Bondo parliamentary seat gathers steam ahead of elections  Siaya women who shunned ‘sex for fish’   Police explore arson angle in county office fire   Fire breaks out at Kisumu's Prosperity House  "They were three children but one of them escaped unhurt and alerted the neighbours who rushed the two to the hospital," said Chebosho.  She added that the two were rushed to Got Agulu hospital where they were pronounced dead on arrival.  The bodies have been moved to Bondo sub-county hospital mortuary awaiting postmortem.   CHILDREN KILLED: Three children die in Siaya house inferno, they included a set of twins  Ready for Exams? Education expert Andiwo Obondo talks on the concerns over strike in school fires  Discussion with Education expert-Andiwo Obondo as Government gears up for gradual school re-opening By Caleb Kingwara | 11 hours ago By James Omoro | 11 hours ago By James Omoro | 1 day ago By Isaiah Gwengi | 1 day ago